post_message: This is my first time attending a hackathon, do you need to have extensive programming experience before entering? If not, what sort of knowledge or experience would I need for the event? Thank you

discussion_topic_message: phave a general question ask hereorp
post_message:
Hi Benny, Welcome! 

You don't have to have extensive programming experience, but some programming experience will help. Take a poke around some of the resources we have included in this site, but otherwise show up with an open mind and looking to learn something. We will do some quick icebreaker activities to help with group formation, so just be honest about your skills and what you can contribute. 

You can take a look at the rubric that we will be using  for 'judging'. Notice, technical excellence and implementation are only 1/3 of the total score. We are also looking for novel projects, and projects that have the potential to positively impact the student experience. 

Best,

Alison

discussion_topic_message: phave a general question ask hereorp
post_message:
Hi,

I am curious as to how would the teams be formed. Would it be based on individual skillset?  Should we team up on our own after the morning session?  

Thanks and Regards,

Gayatri G

discussion_topic_message: phave a general question ask hereorp
post_message: Team formation is up to you! There's no limits on team size, and team are self-formed. If you are looking for a team, talk to the other folks in the room, or make a post here.

discussion_topic_message: phave a general question ask hereorp
post_message:
Hi,

I am also wondering what we need to bring to the hackathon and how to prepare.

Also, I am new to the Canvas API, is there any instruction on how to get the API token? 

Kate

discussion_topic_message: phave a general question ask hereorp
post_message:
Hi Kate,  you should bring: a laptop. We also recommend a mug and water bottle! If you are planning on exploring the API we suggest you take a look at the Canvas API Guidelines.  You can take a look at some resources about the API here: https://canvas.ubc.ca/courses/46341/pages/the-canvas-rest-api?module_item_id=1420237.

We will also give a very quick introduction to the API on Saturday morning. 

Best,

Alison
